      "title": "Advances in Catalyst Deactivation and Regeneration. Catalysts",
      "abstract": "Catalyst deactivation, the loss over time of catalytic activity and/or selectivity, is a problem of great and continuing concern in the practice of industrial catalytic processes. Costs to industry for catalyst replacement and process shutdown total tens of billions of dollars per year. [...]"
